Coffee.

29
00:08:54,365 --> 00:08:55,366
是的,是的,是的。
Yep, yep, yep.

30
00:09:00,985 --> 00:09:01,984
准备好了吗?
Ready?

31
00:10:57,588 --> 00:10:59,949
发生了什么。什么错了吗?
What's going on. What wrong?

32
00:10:59,950 --> 00:11:01,450
想要你的床吗?
Hm, want your bed?

33
00:11:02,295 --> 00:11:03,461
保持冷静。好吧?
Be calm. Okay?

34
00:11:29,232 --> 00:11:30,232
Sh, sh.

35
00:11:42,124 --> 00:11:43,624
没关系。
Sh, sh! It's okay.

36
00:11:45,639 --> 00:11:48,222
没关系。没关系。
It's all right. It's all right.

37
00:12:00,646 --> 00:12:02,236
给我。
Give me that.

38
00:12:04,327 --> 00:12:07,567
不叫我们遇见试探，救我们脱离凶恶。
And lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from evil.

39
00:12:07,568 --> 00:12:09,096
阿们。阿们。
Amen. Amen.

40
00:12:09,097 --> 00:12:12,957
在我们失去更多鸡之前，你去追捕那只该死的土狼。
You go hunt down that damn coyote, before we lose any more of our chickens.

41
00:12:22,144 --> 00:12:23,144
嗯,爸爸?
Uh, Pa?

42
00:12:24,008 --> 00:12:25,258
我能和你一起去打猎吗?
Can I come hunt with you?

43
00:12:27,157 --> 00:12:28,776
问你的马。
Ask your ma.

44
00:12:28,777 --> 00:12:30,490
好吧,我能吗?
Well, can I?

45
00:12:35,618 --> 00:12:36,617
我可以吗?
Can I?

46
00:12:40,327 --> 00:12:41,728
如果你做完家务。
If you finish your chores.

47
00:12:48,277 --> 00:12:51,473
打扫我的床，喂贝丝。
Gotta clean my bed, feed Bess.

48
00:13:00,908 --> 00:13:02,170
这是什么?
What's this?

49
00:13:02,171 --> 00:13:03,821
妈妈给我的。
Ma gave it to me.

50
00:13:04,927 --> 00:13:08,681
她说你在700码外射杀了一名红衣少校。
She said you shot a red major clean off his horse at 700 yards.

51
00:13:12,008 --> 00:13:15,160
我想她说过我可以从700码外的马背上射下一个红衣长官。
I think she said I could shoot a red major off his horse 700 yards.

52
00:13:16,148 --> 00:13:17,148
我不能。
I can't.

53
00:13:17,888 --> 00:13:18,888
没有人能做到。
Nobody can.

54
00:13:20,678 --> 00:13:22,777
但你确实杀了杀了雷布。
But you did kill kill Rebs.

55
00:13:22,778 --> 00:13:24,811
这可不是什么礼貌的谈话，孩子。
It ain't polite conversation, son.

56
00:13:25,847 --> 00:13:29,465
你是个神枪手?
You were a sharp shooter?

57
00:13:29,466 --> 00:13:31,177
我还是个神枪手，小子。
I'm still a sharp shooter, boy.

58
00:13:31,178 --> 00:13:33,671
永远不要忘记。晚安。
Don't you ever forget it. Goodnight.

59
00:13:54,338 --> 00:13:58,091
哈蒂·麦卡利斯特，谁能想到呢?
Hattie McAllister, who would've thought?

60
00:13:59,289 --> 00:14:10,558
烤辫子的时候，我们常常在你爸爸的店里吃糖果，看书想着有一天我们会在这个狂野的国家拥有最好的辫子。
Grilling pigtails, we used to eat candy and read books in the back of your daddy's store that someday we'd be homesteading this wild country with the best of them.

61
00:14:13,404 --> 00:14:16,259
我们能逃出去吗?
Are we gonna make it out here?

62
00:14:16,260 --> 00:14:17,822
只要有一点勇气。
Just gotta have a little grit.

63
00:14:18,934 --> 00:14:21,071
我都不知道去哪儿找了。
I don't know where to find that anymore.

64
00:14:22,986 --> 00:14:24,277
相信你做的事。
Sure you do.

65
00:14:24,278 --> 00:14:25,278
我知道。
I know.

66
00:14:26,199 --> 00:14:29,375
内心深处，你是这片土地上最坚强的女人。
Deep down, you're the toughest woman in this territory.

67
00:19:03,278 --> 00:19:06,164
爸爸在半英里外打死了那只郊狼。
Pa shot that coyote from half mile away.

68
00:19:08,770 --> 00:19:10,720
大概有100码吧。
Oh, it was more like 100 yards.

69
00:19:15,341 --> 00:19:19,300
天啊,帽子。到底发生了什么?
Good Lord, Hat. What the hell happened?

70
00:19:21,277 --> 00:19:22,277
马?
Ma?

71
00:19:41,711 --> 00:19:44,024
孩子睡了，晚饭也准备好了。
Boy's down. Supper's put away.

72
00:19:46,991 --> 00:19:48,490
我很抱歉。
I'm sorry.

73
00:19:48,491 --> 00:19:51,460
他们一定是在居留地外找什么东西。
They must have wandered off the reservation looking for something.

74
00:19:51,461 --> 00:19:52,461
没有取消。
Got no scrap.

75
00:20:00,262 --> 00:20:04,823
我想回家。
I want to go home.

76
00:20:04,824 --> 00:20:10,540
好吧，如果你想见你父母，我可以在铁路公司找份工作。
All right, if you wanna see your folks, reckon I can get a work with the railroad.

77
00:20:10,541 --> 00:20:11,541
给你买张票。
Buy you a ticket.

78
00:20:12,342 --> 00:20:13,543
我不想要票。
I don't want a ticket.

79
00:20:14,411 --> 00:20:18,644
我想收拾行李带着我们的孩子离开这个被上帝遗弃的地方。
I want to pack the wagon and take our children out of this God forsaken place.

80
00:20:21,792 --> 00:20:24,760
我知道这很难，但这里是好地方。
I know it's been hard, but this here's good land.

81
00:20:24,761 --> 00:20:26,204
我们住在小屋里杰布
We live in a shack, Jeb.

82
00:20:27,641 --> 00:20:33,401
我们有旧的工具，破旧的牲畜，只能用从商店贷款借来的食物来养活我们的孩子。
We've got old tools, worn out live stock, and can only feed our children with food borrowed off store credit.

83
00:20:36,011 --> 00:20:37,874
我知道这很艰难。
I understand it's been tough.

84
00:20:40,632 --> 00:20:42,730
但这是我们的梦想，海蒂。
But this is our dream, Hattie.

85
00:20:42,731 --> 00:20:46,851
这就是我们要做的，在我们自己的土地上建造一个家。
This is what we set out to do, build a home on land we can call our own.

86
00:20:48,522 --> 00:20:50,472
我想让你去找我爸爸找份工作。
I want you to ask my daddy for a job.

87
00:20:52,631 --> 00:20:55,330
你想让我们回到他身边吗?
You want us to crawl back to him?

88
00:20:55,331 --> 00:20:57,011
我们靠自己是做不到的。
We can't make it on our own.

89
00:20:57,012 --> 00:20:59,462
当然，我们可以。我们只需要继续前进。
Hell, yes, we can. We just gotta keep on going.

90
00:21:01,558 --> 00:21:02,891
好吧,我不能。
Well, I can't.

91
00:21:16,284 --> 00:21:17,951
这很好。
That's good.

92
00:21:23,712 --> 00:21:26,501
我要进城去，拿些补给。
I'm gonna ahead into town, grab supplies.

93
00:21:26,502 --> 00:21:27,335
做一个坚强的男孩。
Be a strong boy.

94
00:21:27,336 --> 00:21:30,458
我在城里的时候，你要照顾你妈妈，好吗?
Look after your mom while I'm in town, won't ya?

95
00:21:43,947 --> 00:21:44,947
在这里,Pa。
Here, Pa.

96
00:22:06,245 --> 00:22:10,952
杰布。嗨呀,走吧!
Jeb. Hiyah, go!

97
00:22:45,167 --> 00:22:47,801
我认为这是我们应得的。
I think we've earned it.

98
00:22:47,802 --> 00:22:52,606
爸爸说糖果是一种真正的享受，只有在圣诞节和葬礼上才有。
Pa says candy's a real treat, just for Christmas and funerals.

99
00:22:55,182 --> 00:22:57,766
我小时候住在圣路易斯，我们每周都吃糖。
When I was a girl in St. Louis, we'd have candy every week.

100
00:22:58,603 --> 00:22:59,982
真的吗?
Really?

101
00:22:59,983 --> 00:23:06,101
夏天吃冰淇淋，秋天吃太妃糖，圣诞节吃薄荷棒。
We'd have ice cream in the summer, toffee in the fall and peppermint sticks at Christmas.

102
00:23:06,102 --> 00:23:07,703
你会喜欢住在那里的。
You would've loved living there.

103
00:23:10,483 --> 00:23:13,402
爷爷奶奶不让你嫁给爸爸，是真的吗?
Is it true that Granny and Gramps didn't want you to marry Pa?

104
00:23:14,742 --> 00:23:18,072
他们只是对我想要什么有自己的想法。
They just had their own ideas about what they wanted for me.

105
00:23:18,073 --> 00:23:22,271
但爸爸是个英雄。他保卫密苏里不被叛军占领。
But PA's a hero. He defended Missouri from the Rebs.

106
00:23:22,272 --> 00:23:23,599
你爸是叛军。
Your pa was a Reb.

107
00:23:25,693 --> 00:23:27,943
他曾用它来联合起来拯救联邦。
He used it to be join up to save the Union.

108
00:23:30,372 --> 00:23:32,072
那时候的事情并不简单。
Things weren't simple back then.

109
00:23:34,183 --> 00:23:35,183
Will.

110
00:24:09,566 --> 00:24:11,712
我可能会给你一个美好的早晨，女士。
I might fine morning to you, ma'am.

111
00:24:11,713 --> 00:24:13,362
和你。
And to you.

112
00:24:13,363 --> 00:24:17,446
不知道能不能麻烦你给我们点水。
I wonder if we might trouble you for some of your water.

113
00:24:18,493 --> 00:24:22,062
我们的坐骑快干了，我们也好不到哪里去。
Our mounts are about dried out and we're not much better.

114
00:24:22,063 --> 00:24:23,413
你想拿多少就拿多少。
Take as much as you like.

115
00:24:24,704 --> 00:24:25,817
感谢。
Much obliged.

116
00:24:40,033 --> 00:24:41,033
Will.

117
00:24:49,633 --> 00:24:51,853
你怎么了，孩子。
What's the matter with you, son.

118
00:24:51,854 --> 00:24:53,704
你妈没教你什么礼貌吗?
Didn't your ma teach you any manners?

119
00:24:55,813 --> 00:25:00,716
我听说你没有妈妈，从妓女那里辍学，被毛皮商养大。
You didn't have no ma, dropped out of a whore and raised by those fur traders, is what I heard.

120
00:25:02,967 --> 00:25:04,516
非常抱歉，夫人。
I do apologize, ma'am.

121
00:25:05,503 --> 00:25:10,603
到现在为止，我们已经有三个月左右的时间了，恐怕这一点已经开始显现出来了。
We have been in the saddle for about three months now and I'm afraid it is beginning to show.

122
00:25:10,604 --> 00:25:19,453
我没办法，但是注意到你那边的鸡笼，我，我在想我能不能买些腌猪肉或者一打鸡蛋。
Um, I couldn't help, but notice your coop over yonder, I, I wonder if I might offer to buy some salt pork and maybe a dozen eggs.

123
00:25:19,454 --> 00:25:20,854
你需要多少就拿多少。
Fetch as many as you need.

124
00:25:23,995 --> 00:25:24,995
好。
Well.

125
00:25:26,894 --> 00:25:31,067
我必须承认，我觉得和一位女士谈生意有点鲁莽。
I must confess, I, I do feel a bit forward talking business with a lady.

126
00:25:31,999 --> 00:25:33,796
你丈夫在家吗?
Uh, is your husband at home?

127
00:25:35,444 --> 00:25:38,027
他不是在这里。他进城去了。
He ain't here. He gone to town.

128
00:25:41,023 --> 00:25:46,104
哦，好吧，我想那你就是家里的男人了。
Oh, well then I guess that makes you the man of the house, I reckon.

129
00:25:56,564 --> 00:25:58,547
哦，还有一件事。
Oh, uh, one more thing.

130
00:25:59,504 --> 00:26:02,473
我听出来你是密苏里口音吗。
Is that a Missouri accent that I detect.

131
00:26:02,474 --> 00:26:03,733
圣路易斯。
St. Louis.

132
00:26:03,734 --> 00:26:07,183
我知道它。真是太巧了。
I knew it. What a happy coincidence.

133
00:26:07,184 --> 00:26:14,462
我自己也是卡梅伦派的，那边那个大块头，他来自阿肯色州，但我们尽量不以此为借口。
I am a Cameron man, myself, that big fella over there, he's from Arkansas, but we try not to hold that against it.

134
00:26:16,424 --> 00:26:19,183
密苏里州这边来的人不多。
We don't get many Missourians out this way.

135
00:26:19,184 --> 00:26:20,837
不，夫人，我想你不知道。
No, ma'am, I expect you don't.

136
00:26:30,128 --> 00:26:35,129
我很乐意在你们走之前给你们做点早餐。
I'd be happy to cook you men some breakfast before you go.

137
00:26:36,105 --> 00:26:39,527
好吧，我们将不胜感激。
Well, we would be much obliged.

138
00:26:50,024 --> 00:26:51,624
您真是太好了，夫人。
This is very kind of you, ma'am.

139
00:27:04,515 --> 00:27:07,033
那边是你的家人吗，太太?
Those your folks over there, Mrs. Uh?

140
00:27:07,034 --> 00:27:08,563
麦卡利斯特。麦卡利斯特。
McAllister. McAllister.

141
00:27:08,564 --> 00:27:11,538
海蒂。这是贝丝，这是威尔。
Hattie. This is Bess and this is Will.

142
00:27:12,525 --> 00:27:13,525
设置表。
Set the table.

143
00:27:17,564 --> 00:27:18,794
你多大了?
How old are you?

144
00:27:18,795 --> 00:27:20,894
九又四分之三。
Nine and three quarters.

145
00:27:20,895 --> 00:27:24,497
那么，我想它应该够大，可以戴这个了。
Why then, I reckon that's big enough to wear one of these.

146
00:27:30,705 --> 00:27:34,183
你的家真漂亮，麦卡利斯特太太。
This is a lovely home you have here, Mrs. McAllister.

147
00:27:34,184 --> 00:27:35,688
你丈夫是个幸运的人。
Your husband is a lucky man.

148
00:27:46,095 --> 00:27:48,644
她想说话。
She wants to talk.

149
00:27:48,645 --> 00:27:50,508
哦，现在，让我来。
Oh, now here, allow me.

150
00:27:52,124 --> 00:27:53,875
我这辈子就抱过两岁的孩子。
I've held a baby at two in my life.

151
00:27:55,216 --> 00:27:57,614
是的。你没事吧?
Yeah. You okay?

152
00:27:57,615 --> 00:27:58,615
是的。
Yeah.

153
