155
00:28:33,040 --> 00:28:39,703
现在永远的迪克西她从未失去过什么，贝丝。
Now Dixie forever She's never had a loss Bess.

156
00:28:39,704 --> 00:28:45,041
下了老鹰，上了十字架我要去拿些鸡蛋。
Down with the eagle And up with the cross Gonna go fetch some eggs.

157
00:28:45,042 --> 00:28:50,305
我们会团结在旗帜周围，男孩们我们会再次团结起来耶。来吧。
We will rally round the flag, boys We'll rally 'round again Yeah. Come on.

158
00:28:51,327 --> 00:28:56,565
呼喊，呼喊，自由的战斗口号嘿，嘿。嘿。
Shout shout The battle cry of freedom Hey, Hey. Hey.

159
00:28:56,566 --> 00:28:57,678
那是瑞贝卡的歌吗?
Is that a Reb song?

160
00:29:09,281 --> 00:29:11,925
得教她那首歌。
Need to teach her that song.

161
00:29:11,926 --> 00:29:14,295
你以前从没听过这首歌。
You never heard that song before.

162
00:29:14,296 --> 00:29:15,379
你喜欢那首歌吗?
You like that song?

163
00:30:06,134 --> 00:30:08,076
快乐的女孩现在，嘟，嘟
Happy girl now, doo, doo

164
00:30:12,079 --> 00:30:14,193
她是个多么温柔的小女孩啊。
What a gentle little soul she is.

165
00:30:18,022 --> 00:30:20,810
你对雷布没什么意见，对吧，孩子。
You ain' got a problem with Rebs, now do you, boy.

166
00:30:23,326 --> 00:30:27,495
我们年轻的主人是在战争结束后出生的。
Our young host was born after hostilities ended.

167
00:30:27,496 --> 00:30:30,290
我相信他是个自豪的美国人，对吧，孩子。
I'm sure he's a proud American, aren't you, boy.

168
00:30:31,636 --> 00:30:35,745
这没有错，人应该忠于自己的国家。
Nothing wrong with that, man should be loyal to his own country.

169
00:30:35,746 --> 00:30:36,746
不是每个人都是。
Not everybody is.

170
00:30:38,717 --> 00:30:40,905
我爸爸是个神枪手。
My daddy was a sharp shooter.

171
00:30:40,906 --> 00:30:41,906
他现在吗?
Was he now?

172
00:30:43,276 --> 00:30:45,795
威尔的枪法也不错。
Will's not a bad shot himself.

173
00:30:45,796 --> 00:30:49,127
不如你去给这些先生们看看你爸爸给你买的猎枪。
Why don't you go show these gentlemen that shotgun your daddy got you.

174
00:30:59,123 --> 00:31:00,945
放松
Easy now. Oh, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

175
00:31:00,946 --> 00:31:02,229
让我看看。
Let me see that.

176
00:31:03,153 --> 00:31:04,504
哦我的天哪。
Oh my goodness.

177
00:31:08,626 --> 00:31:11,362
那些叛军来这里最好小心点。
Those Rebs best be careful coming around here.

178
00:31:11,363 --> 00:31:16,364
哦。
Oh.

179
00:31:18,586 --> 00:31:20,506
威尔，把咖啡热一下。
Will, warm up the coffee.

180
00:31:32,087 --> 00:31:33,646
希望你喜欢草莓酱。
Hope you like strawberry jam.

181
00:31:33,647 --> 00:31:35,446
今年春天我们只能种这个了。
That's all we could grow this spring.

182
00:31:35,447 --> 00:31:37,429
我相信我们都很喜欢。
Oh, I'm sure we like it just fine.

183
00:31:39,737 --> 00:31:43,400
在开饭之前，孩子们，我们想先祈祷一下。
Before we dig in, boys, we like to have a little prayer.

184
00:31:44,657 --> 00:31:45,679
我们保持谦卑。
Keep us humble.

185
00:31:47,777 --> 00:32:03,166
主啊，求你看顾我们，帮助我们感谢上帝赐予我们的这些恩赐，帮助我们时刻留意别人的需要，而不是只考虑自己。
Lord, please look down on us and help us to be grateful for these gifts that we have been given and help us to be always mindful of the needs of others and not think only of ourselves.

186
00:32:03,167 --> 00:32:06,526
我们以你儿子耶稣基督的名义祈祷。
We pray in the name of your son, Jesus Christ.

187
00:32:06,527 --> 00:32:08,656
阿们。阿们。
Amen. Amen.

188
00:32:08,657 --> 00:32:09,598
好吧。
All right.

189
00:32:09,599 --> 00:32:12,859
马!
Ma!

190
00:32:15,377 --> 00:32:19,610
威尔，和你妹妹到炉子后面去。现在!
Will, get behind the stove with your sister. Now!

191
00:32:31,518 --> 00:32:34,070
一定是有什么误会，夫人。
There must be some misunderstanding, ma'am.

192
00:32:34,997 --> 00:32:36,200
我们得罪了谁?
How have we offended?

193
00:32:39,828 --> 00:32:41,780
我不会在家里喂杀手。
I don't feed killers in my house.

194
00:32:42,887 --> 00:32:43,887
杀手。
Killers.

195
00:32:45,197 --> 00:32:48,481
良好的耶和华说的。
Good Lord.

196
00:32:48,482 --> 00:32:50,297
哦，哦，我明白你的困惑了。
Oh, oh, I see the confusion.

197
00:32:50,298 --> 00:32:55,850
天啊，她说的是我们从拉勒米堡附近的夏安族商人那里拿到的那些奖杯。
Boy, she is talking about those trophies that we got off that Cheyenne trader near Fort Laramie.

198
00:32:57,438 --> 00:33:04,306
女士，我知道这是一桩不体面的买卖，但当你在边远地区交易时，这些东西可能很值钱。
Ma'am, I realize that's an unseemly business, but those can be very valuable objects when you're trading in the back country.

199
00:33:04,307 --> 00:33:09,976
我们就不能坐下来谈点愉快的事吗。
Now can't we just sit back down and talk about something more pleasant.

200
00:33:09,977 --> 00:33:11,660
我们玩得很开心。
We were having such a nice time.

201
00:33:13,817 --> 00:33:15,471
我觉得你最好现在就走。
I think it's best you go now.

202
00:33:17,928 --> 00:33:20,176
我们还在等什么?
What the hell are we waiting for?

203
00:33:20,177 --> 00:33:22,040
她只有两发子弹。
She's only got two rounds.

204
00:33:28,847 --> 00:33:30,586
如你所愿。
As you wish.

205
00:33:30,587 --> 00:33:32,081
把枪留下。
And leave your guns.

206
00:33:34,308 --> 00:33:35,308
我们才不会呢。
The hell we will.

207
00:33:36,288 --> 00:33:40,851
女士，我相信你知道这些武器有多值钱。
Ma'am, I'm sure you understand how valuable these weapons are.

208
00:33:42,318 --> 00:33:44,631
你可以用你的头皮换些新的。
You can trade your scalps for some new ones.

209
00:33:52,788 --> 00:33:53,888
你听到那个女人说的了。
You heard the woman.

210
00:34:01,818 --> 00:34:03,767
这些是我爸爸的。
Uh-uh, these were my pa's.

211
00:34:03,768 --> 00:34:06,020
他们把他从豌豆岭的尸体上带走了。
They took him off his dead body of Pea Ridge.

212
00:34:10,428 --> 00:34:11,428
很好。
Fine.

213
00:34:20,878 --> 00:34:22,401
我能拿我的帽子吗?
Can I have my hat?

214
00:34:23,899 --> 00:34:25,148
威尔，把帽子给他。
Will, give him his hat.

215
00:35:20,441 --> 00:35:21,941
嗨呀!
Hiyah!

216
00:35:56,352 --> 00:35:57,352
帮助我。
Help me.

217
00:36:06,517 --> 00:36:07,516
推动!推动!
Push! Push!

218
00:36:42,935 --> 00:36:46,153
狗娘养的!
Son of a bitch!

219
00:36:46,986 --> 00:36:48,069
啊,下来!
Ah, get down!

220
00:36:56,954 --> 00:36:57,954
等一秒!来看看!
Wait a sec! Come and see!

221
00:36:59,505 --> 00:37:03,024
来看看!
Come and see!

222
00:37:03,025 --> 00:37:08,025
狗娘养的!
Son of a bitch!

223
00:38:08,242 --> 00:38:11,297
Hyah !你到底在干什么?
Hyah! What the hell are you doing?

224
00:38:11,298 --> 00:38:12,715
我要活的!
I want 'em alive!

225
00:38:18,189 --> 00:38:19,753
哇!她根本不会开枪。
Whoo! She can't shoot for jack shit.

226
00:38:24,394 --> 00:38:26,555
我需要你勇敢一点。好吧?
I need you to be brave. Okay?

227
00:38:26,556 --> 00:38:27,556
好吧。
Okay.

228
00:38:28,310 --> 00:38:29,310
重新加载。
Reload.

229
00:38:30,170 --> 00:38:31,420
照顾好你妹妹。
Take care of your sister.

230
00:40:40,641 --> 00:40:42,564
拿上你想要的，走吧。
Just take what you want and go.

231
00:41:11,078 --> 00:41:14,495
但我们想要的是你。
But what we want is you.

232
00:41:27,454 --> 00:41:29,060
我可以做任何事。
I can do anything.

233
00:41:29,061 --> 00:41:32,455
跟踪，射杀水牛，管理团队。
Lay track, shoot buffalo, run the teams.

234
00:41:33,352 --> 00:41:36,050
谢谢你的关心，麦卡利斯特先生。
I appreciate the interest, Mr. McAllister.

235
00:41:36,051 --> 00:41:37,971
根本没有工作。
There simply isn't the work.

236
00:41:37,972 --> 00:41:40,491
我们有足够的人来满足我们的需要。
We have more than enough men to meet our needs.

237
00:41:40,492 --> 00:41:41,871
一定会有办法的。
There has to be something.

238
00:41:41,872 --> 00:41:44,060
我甚至可以帮你弄马车。
I could even help with the chuck wagons.

239
00:41:44,061 --> 00:41:46,400
哦，上帝，我们不是牛仔。
Oh Lord, we're not cowboys.

240
00:41:46,401 --> 00:41:48,652
我们只是把食物从下游运上来。
We just bring our food up from down the line.

241
00:41:50,452 --> 00:41:52,162
美好的一天。最好的运气。
Good day. Best of luck.

242
00:42:17,908 --> 00:42:21,157
你都是对的。没关系。
You're all right. It's okay.

243
00:42:22,689 --> 00:42:23,689
我们开始吧。
Here we go.

244
00:42:25,776 --> 00:42:26,776
好吧。好吧。
Okay. Okay.

245
00:42:30,621 --> 00:42:33,063
麦卡利斯特太太。
Mrs. McAllister.

246
00:42:43,607 --> 00:42:45,190
隐藏你的妹妹。
Hide your sister.

247
00:43:06,893 --> 00:43:09,835
麦卡利斯特太太。这是远远不够。
Mrs. McAllister. That's far enough.

248
00:43:12,022 --> 00:43:14,273
我很遗憾我们一开始就搞砸了。
I regret that we got off on the wrong foot.

249
00:43:16,223 --> 00:43:19,495
我希望我们能重新开始，重新来过。
I would like for us to start over, make it right.

250
00:43:21,832 --> 00:43:26,935
没什么好谈的，除了你们这些人骑上马走了。
There's nothing to talk about, except you men getting on your horses and riding off.

251
00:43:28,222 --> 00:43:38,485
我尊重你的感受，我也很同情你，但这次对峙对谁都没好处。
I respect how you must be feeling and I can sympathize, but this standoff not doing anybody a lick of good.

252
00:43:42,293 --> 00:43:46,465
的确，我在战争期间和战争后都杀过不少人。
It's true that I've done my share of killing both during the war and after.

253
00:43:47,902 --> 00:43:53,426
但有一件事我从没做过，我从没伤害过女人或孩子。
But one thing I ain't never done, I ain't never hurt a woman or a child.

254
00:43:54,982 --> 00:43:57,333
我为什么要相信你说的话。
Why should I believe a word you say.

255
00:44:03,442 --> 00:44:04,735
我曾经有过一个女儿。
I had a daughter once.

256
00:44:06,653 --> 00:44:10,526
她是我唯一的孩子，我的掌上明珠。
She was my only child, apple of my eye.

257
00:44:16,463 --> 00:44:20,546
我把一个父亲所能给予的每一点爱和感情都慷慨地给予了那个孩子。
Every bit of love and affection a father can give I lavished on that child.

258
00:44:25,283 --> 00:44:26,426
现在她死了。
She's dead now.

259
00:44:28,853 --> 00:44:30,266
埋在卡梅隆的坟里。
Buried out Cameron way.

260
00:44:38,033 --> 00:44:45,533
我对着她的坟墓发誓，我不会伤害你和你孩子的一根头发。
I swear on her grave, I will not harm a hair on your head or on the heads of your children.

261
00:44:54,143 --> 00:44:55,143
该死的!
Dammit!

262
00:45:02,243 --> 00:45:03,243
该死的傻瓜!
Damn fools!

263
00:45:13,843 --> 00:45:15,594
你没事吧?你没事吧?
You okay? You okay?

264
00:45:42,864 --> 00:45:46,059
对不起,妈妈。我不是故意吵醒她的。
I'm sorry, Mom. I didn't mean to wake her.

265
00:45:46,060 --> 00:45:47,585
没关系。
That's all right.

266
00:45:47,586 --> 00:45:48,906
让她在这里。
Bring her here.

267
00:46:19,824 --> 00:46:20,991
来吧,贝丝。
Come on, Bess.

268
00:46:28,077 --> 00:46:29,757
他们对黛西做了什么?
What are they doing with Daisy?

269
00:46:37,944 --> 00:46:38,944
不。
No.

270
00:46:41,359 --> 00:46:42,359
不!
No!

271
00:46:44,858 --> 00:46:46,157
不。
No.

272
00:47:12,024 --> 00:47:15,367
对不起。
Sorry.

273
00:47:22,022 --> 00:47:22,855
现在，你抱着他。
Now, you hold him.

274
00:47:22,856 --> 00:47:26,069
见鬼，上尉，它会自己好起来的。
Oh, hell, Captain, it'll heal itself.

275
00:47:26,070 --> 00:47:28,005
它会自己痊愈的，舰长。
It'll heal on its own, Captain.

276
00:47:28,006 --> 00:47:30,113
它会自己愈合的。
It'll heal on its own.

277
00:47:30,114 --> 00:47:32,659
耶稣，约瑟夫和玛丽，不。
Jesus, Joseph and Mary, no.

278
00:47:32,660 --> 00:47:35,838
请不要亵渎神明。
Please refrain from that papist blasphemy.

279
00:47:35,839 --> 00:47:37,063
打开他的袖子。
Open his sleeve.

280
00:47:37,064 --> 00:47:41,762
让他们都见鬼去吧!
Damn them all to hell!

281
00:47:41,763 --> 00:47:51,936
我看今世的一切苦难，若与将来要显在我们身上的荣耀相比，就都不足了。
Well I reckon that all the sufferings of this present age are not worthy compared to the glory, which shall be revealed in us.

282
00:47:56,626 --> 00:47:59,159
会没事的。
It's gonna be all right.

283
00:47:59,160 --> 00:48:03,384
爸爸不可能是雷布，妈妈，就是不可能。
Pa couldn't have been Reb, Ma, just couldn't have been.

284
00:48:03,385 --> 00:48:05,035
这就是你生气的原因?
That's what you're upset about?

285
00:48:07,702 --> 00:48:10,888
你爸不是叛徒。
Your Pa's no Rebel.

286
00:48:11,725 --> 00:48:16,287
他开始为南方而战，但他以爱国者的身份结束了这场战争。
He may have begun fighting for the South, but he ended that war a patriot.

287
00:48:19,170 --> 00:48:23,040
但你说过他-好坏并不总是那么清楚，威尔。
But you said that he was- Good and bad aren't always so clear, Will.

288
00:48:24,265 --> 00:48:28,134
有时候你醒来发现自己站在了错误的一边。
Sometimes you wake up and you realize you're on the wrong side of things.

289
00:48:28,135 --> 00:48:32,214
当你爸爸找到他的时候，他有勇气纠正错误。
And when you pa did, he have the courage to make things right.

290
00:48:32,215 --> 00:48:33,598
就像他一直做的那样。
Just like he always does.

291
00:48:41,125 --> 00:48:46,708
等他回来，外面的杀手会感受到上帝的愤怒。
And when he comes back, those killers outside are gonna feel God's wrath.

292
00:48:50,005 --> 00:48:51,958
如果他们杀了他呢?
What if they kill him instead?

293
00:49:19,226 --> 00:49:20,309
快吃吧，孩子。
Better eat up, son.

294
00:49:22,468 --> 00:49:24,748
饿着肚子是很难勇敢的。
Hard to be brave on an empty belly.

295
00:49:29,666 --> 00:49:33,208
队长,还有,
Well, Captain, there's,

296
00:49:35,816 --> 00:49:40,108
关于这一切，有些事我不太明白。
there's just something about all this that I don't rightly understand.

297
00:49:43,495 --> 00:49:44,496
继续。
Go on.

298
00:49:45,416 --> 00:49:49,288
你只说了不要伤害女人和孩子。
Well, it's all you said about not hurting women or kids.

299
00:49:54,146 --> 00:49:56,246
你认为我们应该坚持这一点。
And you think we ought to stand by that.

300
00:50:04,706 --> 00:50:10,945
你还记得你爸爸和我骑马去保卫我们的生活方式不受暴君林肯的迫害。
You remember when your Pappy and I rode out to defend our way of life from the tyrant Lincoln.

301
00:50:10,946 --> 00:50:11,946
我做的事。
I do.

302
00:50:13,886 --> 00:50:23,429
我们当时有很多关于骑士精神和荣誉以及战争应该是什么样子的好想法。
We had a lot of fine ideas then about chivalry and honor and what war should look like.

303
00:50:25,346 --> 00:50:29,579
我们正义的事业如何带领我们走向胜利。
How the rightness of our cause would carry us to victory.

304
00:50:35,486 --> 00:50:38,879
北方佬偷了我们的牛。
And the Yankees stole our cattle.

305
00:50:40,976 --> 00:50:46,229
他们无故烧毁我们的农场，吊死我们的亲人。
They burned our farms and hung our kin without cause.

306
00:50:47,966 --> 00:50:56,566
我们所有美好的想法，在他们贪婪、凶残的仇恨面前，都算不了什么。
And all our fine notions were nothing in the face of their rapacious, murderous hatred.

307
00:51:06,116 --> 00:51:07,919
他们夺走了我唯一的孩子，
They took my only child from me,

308
00:51:12,327 --> 00:51:14,046
剥夺了她的生命
ripped her from this life

309
00:51:16,766 --> 00:51:18,479
毫无怜悯或怜悯之心。
without mercy or pity.

310
00:51:23,036 --> 00:51:30,547
世上没有法律，天堂也没有，地狱也没有
And there ain't no law on earth or in heaven or hell

311
00:51:33,566 --> 00:51:37,800
这能阻止一个父亲复仇。
that can keep a father from taking his revenge.

312
00:51:41,366 --> 00:51:42,366
不是魔鬼
Not the devil

313
00:51:48,447 --> 00:51:49,860
而不是上帝本人。
and not God himself.

314
00:51:59,250 --> 00:52:01,666
这让事情更清楚了吗?
That make things any clearer?

315
00:52:10,346 --> 00:52:12,797
反正我们也不会伤害任何人。
Hell, we ain't gonna have to hurt anybody anyway.

316
00:52:16,917 --> 00:52:18,060
你怎么知道的?
How you figure that?

317
00:52:21,207 --> 00:52:24,090
麦卡利斯特太太不适合这种生活。
Mrs. McAllister ain't cut out for this kinda life.

318
00:52:26,067 --> 00:52:28,109
我看她的眼睛就知道了。
I can tell that by looking in her eyes.

319
00:52:30,087 --> 00:52:34,590
我们给她足够的时间，她就会出来找我们。
We give her enough time, she's just gonna come on out here to us.

320
00:52:37,736 --> 00:52:39,660
这是明智的做法。
That's the sensible thing to do.

321
00:52:41,217 --> 00:52:43,660
她是个通情达理的女人。
And she is a sensible woman.

322
00:52:43,661 --> 00:52:45,150
船长!什么?
Captain! What?

323
00:52:48,177 --> 00:52:49,177
地狱。
The hell.

324
00:52:50,643 --> 00:52:52,476
诅咒!
Damnation!

325
00:53:16,762 --> 00:53:18,212
他们在几英里外都能看到。
They'll see that for miles.

326
00:53:25,390 --> 00:53:26,756
马!
Ma!

327
00:53:26,757 --> 00:53:28,309
保持燃烧，明白吗?
Keep it burning, you understand?

328
00:53:28,310 --> 00:53:29,829
任何你能找到的东西。
Anything you can find.

329
00:54:26,259 --> 00:54:27,259
看。
Look.

330
00:55:05,271 --> 00:55:10,271
Will，你的妹妹。
Will, your sister.

331
00:55:51,068 --> 00:55:52,485
快来帮忙。
Come to a help.

332
00:55:53,638 --> 00:55:56,138
孩子们还在里面吗?
The children are still inside?

333
00:55:59,489 --> 00:56:00,839
你一个人来吗，邻居?
You come alone, neighbor?

334
00:56:01,949 --> 00:56:04,677
是的，我看到了烟，我骑得很快。
Yeah, I see the smoke, I come riding real fast.

335
00:56:04,678 --> 00:56:06,001
为什么?什么是错的。
Why? What's wrong.

336
00:56:07,709 --> 00:56:10,299
萨姆森先生，不，去找人帮忙。
Mr. Sameson, no, go get help.

337
00:56:13,197 --> 00:56:14,634
寻求帮助!
Get help!

338
00:56:14,635 --> 00:56:16,348
不。我要活捉他。
No. I want him alive.

339
00:56:16,349 --> 00:56:18,952
骑吧，萨姆森先生，骑吧!
Ride, Mr. Sameson, ride!

340
00:57:06,363 --> 00:57:07,197
让它燃烧吧!
Let it burn!

341
00:57:07,198 --> 00:57:09,652
你疯了吗?队长要活捉他们。
Are you crazy? Captain wants them alive.

342
00:57:22,162 --> 00:57:24,260
我只是想帮忙。
Just trying to help.

343
00:58:42,957 --> 00:58:44,790
让他走。
Let him go.

344
00:58:46,740 --> 00:58:49,229
麦卡利斯特太太，我很惊讶。
Mrs. McAllister, I'm surprised.

345
00:58:49,230 --> 00:58:52,713
一个女人大声嚷嚷并继续这样做是有失尊严的。
It does not dignify a woman to holler and carry on such.

346
00:58:53,940 --> 00:58:55,590
他没有对你做任何事。
He hasn't done anything to you.

347
00:58:58,229 --> 00:58:59,729
这是完全正确的。
Well, that is entirely true.

348
00:59:01,020 --> 00:59:06,933
但正如你所见，你的固执让我们都陷入了困境。
But as you see, your obstinance has put us all in a difficult situation.

349
00:59:09,533 --> 00:59:15,573
所以我再次请求你们到这里来，让我们像文明的人一样解决这个问题。
So I'm gonna ask you again to come out here and let us resolve this like civilized people.

350
00:59:16,890 --> 00:59:19,552
海蒂，你待在那儿。
Hattie, you stay there.

351
00:59:19,553 --> 00:59:21,329
他不善于说谎。
He's a no good liar.

352
00:59:21,330 --> 00:59:22,330
他不可信。
He can't be trusted.

353
00:59:23,932 --> 00:59:26,083
当然，你宁愿不文明。
Of course, you'd rather not be civilized.

354
00:59:29,040 --> 00:59:31,113
我将不得不求助于其他方法。
I'll have to resort to other methods.

355
00:59:33,360 --> 00:59:35,340
你不必这么做的。
You don't have to do this.

356
00:59:35,341 --> 00:59:39,333
我希望不会。我是牧师的儿子。
I'd hope not to. See, I'm a preacher's son.

357
00:59:40,320 --> 00:59:42,839
我从小就被教导要相信《圣经》。
I was raised to believe in the Good Book.

358
00:59:42,840 --> 00:59:45,904
这是唯一能让我们不变成野蛮人的东西。
It's the only thing that keeps us from being savages.

359
00:59:47,190 --> 00:59:50,279
但即使是牧师的孩子也有他的极限。
But even a preacher's boy has got his limits.

360
00:59:50,280 --> 00:59:53,434
请。他有一个妻子和五个孩子。
Please. He has a wife and five children.

361
00:59:55,591 --> 00:59:57,299
耶和华是我的牧者。
The Lord is my shepherd.

362
00:59:57,300 --> 00:59:58,300
我不需要。
I shall not want.

363
00:59:59,310 --> 01:00:00,419
你让我躺下。
You made me to lay down.

364
01:00:00,420 --> 01:00:02,310
我不喜欢重复自己的话。
I don't like repeating myself.

365
01:00:02,311 --> 01:00:03,144
他领我在可安歇的水边。
He led me besides the still waters.

366
01:00:03,145 --> 01:00:08,283
麦卡利斯特夫人，我再说一遍。
Mrs. McAllister, so I'm gonna say this one more time.

367
01:00:09,421 --> 01:00:10,281
快点出来!
Come on out!

368
01:00:10,282 --> 01:00:15,249
在死荫的幽谷中，我无所畏惧。
In the valley of the shadow off death, I will fear no evil.

369
01:00:15,250 --> 01:00:16,277
不。不。
No. No.

370
01:00:16,278 --> 01:00:18,069
因为你与我同在。
For thou art with me.

371
01:02:21,872 --> 01:02:23,795
你把它放在街对面了。
You left it across the street.

372
01:02:27,001 --> 01:02:28,001
看到了吗?
See?

373
01:02:30,242 --> 01:02:33,421
也许我最好下来护送你过去。
Maybe I best come down and escort you across.

374
01:02:33,422 --> 01:02:35,398
不，小姐，我很好。
No, miss, I'm quite all right.

375
01:02:41,882 --> 01:02:45,004
嘿。你真打算半醉半醉开车回家吗?
Hey. You really gonna drive home half liquored up?

376
01:02:46,352 --> 01:02:50,855
在我看来，你应该清醒过来，或者继续喝下去，喝个烂醉。
Seems to me you ought to sober up or just go on, get drunk all the way.

377
01:02:53,496 --> 01:02:54,818
我得回我的农场了。
I gotta get home to my farm.

378
01:02:54,819 --> 01:02:58,025
农场吗?你的农场不会想念你的。
Farm? Your farm ain't gonna miss you.

379
01:02:59,012 --> 01:03:01,231
我们的床很不错。
We got real nice beds in there.

380
01:03:01,232 --> 01:03:03,991
软缎子床单。
Soft satin sheets.

381
01:03:03,992 --> 01:03:05,581
哦，你可以睡一整晚。
Oh, you could sleep all night.

382
01:03:05,582 --> 01:03:07,332
早上第一件事就是起床。
Wake up first thing in the morning.

383
01:03:08,522 --> 01:03:10,472
当然，你也可以做其他事情。
Of course, you can do other things too.

384
01:03:11,744 --> 01:03:13,105
我的妻子。
My wife.

385
01:03:13,106 --> 01:03:14,545
你的妻子吗?她在等我。
Your wife? She's waiting on me.

386
01:03:16,072 --> 01:03:20,646
直觉告诉我，你妻子并不欣赏你，
Something tells me your wife, she don't appreciate you,

387
01:03:23,042 --> 01:03:28,042
像你这样努力工作的人，不是你应得的。
hard workin' man like you, not the way you deserve.

388
01:03:30,060 --> 01:03:33,226
哦,天啊!
Oh, geez!

389
01:03:52,068 --> 01:03:53,151
Hyah !
Hyah!

390
01:03:58,144 --> 01:04:00,925
我觉得你该学学怎么煮咖啡了。
I think it's time you learned how to make some coffee.

391
01:04:02,252 --> 01:04:03,502
首先，放一些水。
First, put on some water.

392
01:04:27,752 --> 01:04:29,675
现在我们需要磨碎一些豆子。
Now we need to grind up some beans.

393
01:04:31,233 --> 01:04:33,036
你希望他们像食盐一样好。
You want 'em fine like table salt.

394
01:04:37,562 --> 01:04:38,813
我们可以煮吗?
Can we boil 'em?

395
01:04:39,693 --> 01:04:44,252
这可能就是牛手制作出他们称之为咖啡的黑色污泥的方法，但这不是正确的方法。
That may be how cow hands make some black sludge they call coffee, but it's not the proper way.

396
01:04:44,253 --> 01:04:45,902
我们做了什么不同的事?
Well, what do we do different?

397
01:04:45,903 --> 01:04:47,252
那个苦差事怎么样?
How's that grind looking?

398
01:04:54,513 --> 01:04:56,042
就像盐一样。
Just like salt.

399
01:04:56,043 --> 01:04:57,212
好。
Good.

400
01:04:57,213 --> 01:04:59,313
现在找点东西做过滤器。
Now find something we can use as a filter.

401
01:05:28,923 --> 01:05:30,273
现在我们等它沸腾。
Now we wait for it to boil.

402
01:05:32,374 --> 01:05:34,223
你想知道我和你爸是怎么认识的吗?
You wanna know how your pa and I met?

403
01:05:38,193 --> 01:05:41,044
有一天，我在圣路易斯放学回家的路上。
I was walking home from school one day back in St. Louis.

404
01:05:42,243 --> 01:05:46,082
那是在战争期间，街上到处都是士兵。
It was during the war and the streets were full of soldiers.

405
01:05:46,083 --> 01:05:48,123
有一群人决定找点乐子。
One bunch decided they wanted to have some fun.

406
01:05:48,124 --> 01:05:51,932
所以他们偷了我的书。
So they stole my books.

407
01:05:51,933 --> 01:05:54,062
我恳求他们把它们还给我。
I begged and pleaded for them to give 'em back.

408
01:05:54,063 --> 01:05:55,063
但是他们不会。
But they wouldn't.

409
01:05:56,912 --> 01:06:01,176
就在我开始哭的时候，我听到有人命令那些男孩停下来。
And just when I started to cry, I heard someone order those boys to stop.

410
01:06:02,163 --> 01:06:06,787
我本以为会是中尉或上尉，结果只有你爸。
I turned around expecting a lieutenant or a captain, but it was just your pa.

411
01:06:08,824 --> 01:06:13,386
他孤身一人，穿着士兵的制服。
He was all alone, in a private's uniform no less.

412
01:06:15,424 --> 01:06:26,257
这是一个人对六个人，但他的声音里有某种东西，某种东西表明他仍然可以把他们每一个人都舔一遍，一次一个，或者一起舔一遍。
There was one man against six, but there was something in his voice, something that said he could still lick every single one of them, one at a time or all together.

413
01:06:28,174 --> 01:06:34,777
他们听到后，一个接一个地走开了，直到最后一个，把书还给我，向我道歉。
When they heard it, one by one, they started to drift away till the last one, gave me back my books and apologized.

414
01:06:38,583 --> 01:06:42,003
你爸问我能不能送我回家。
Your pa asked me if he could walk me home.

415
01:06:42,004 --> 01:06:45,397
我说，是的，但我心里已经知道了。
I said, yes, but in my heart, I already knew.

416
01:06:47,999 --> 01:06:49,000
知道什么?
Knew what?

417
01:06:53,372 --> 01:06:56,705
他就是我想嫁的人。
That he was the man I wanted to marry.

418
01:06:57,584 --> 01:07:04,507
这个世界上没有什么能让他放弃，无论发生什么，他都会站起来保护我。
That nothing in this world could ever cause him to give up and whatever would come, he would stand up and protect me.

419
01:07:11,614 --> 01:07:14,617
好了，现在把它倒在豆子上，慢慢地。
All right, now pour it over the beans, nice and slow.

420
01:07:35,674 --> 01:07:37,533
再来点冰糖怎么样?
How about some more rock candy?

421
01:07:37,534 --> 01:07:39,484
黑咖啡是骗不了你的，对吧?
Can't trick your coffee black, can you?

422
01:08:00,444 --> 01:08:01,444
Will. Will!

423
01:08:03,964 --> 01:08:05,214
我需要你去放哨。
I need you to keep watch.

424
01:08:12,064 --> 01:08:13,504
我马上回来。
I'll be right back.

425
01:08:23,804 --> 01:08:24,848
嘘,嘘!
Psst, psst!

426
01:08:28,175 --> 01:08:29,175
马!
Ma!

427
01:08:32,584 --> 01:08:33,585
不要开枪。
Don't shoot.

428
01:08:35,135 --> 01:08:36,278
我只是来谈话的。
I just come the talk.

429
01:08:38,675 --> 01:08:42,538
你要是敢退缩我发誓，我就一枪崩了你。
You so much as flinch and I swear, I'll put a bullet through your heart.

430
01:08:43,475 --> 01:08:44,475
我不是武装。
I ain't armed.

431
01:08:46,445 --> 01:08:48,334
直穿你的心脏。
Right through your heart.

432
01:08:48,335 --> 01:08:49,334
请。
Please.

433
01:08:52,145 --> 01:08:54,107
其他人不知道我来了。
The others don't know I come.

434
01:08:54,108 --> 01:08:55,158
你能听我说吗?
Will you just listen?

435
01:08:57,875 --> 01:08:59,024
好吧。然后说话。
All right. Talk then.

436
01:09:01,287 --> 01:09:03,664
这可不是我想要加入的。
This ain't what I thought I was joining.

437
01:09:03,665 --> 01:09:08,318
我们应该抢银行和火车，而不是伤害妇女和儿童。
We was supposed to rob banks and trains, not hurt women and children.

438
01:09:10,835 --> 01:09:12,835
我再也无法接受了。
It just don't sit right with me no more.

439
01:09:13,955 --> 01:09:16,384
你支持我杀我邻居的原因。
You stood by why I killed my neighbor.

440
01:09:16,385 --> 01:09:20,375
如果我说了什么，我也会死在地上。
If I'd done said anything, I'd be lying dead on the ground too.

441
01:09:23,135 --> 01:09:27,128
我记得我妈妈曾经警告我不要结交坏朋友。
I remember my mama once warned me about falling in with bad company.

442
01:09:28,715 --> 01:09:32,708
当我这么做的时候，我没有意识到分手是多么的难。
Once I did, I didn't realize how hard it would be to part ways.

443
01:09:34,896 --> 01:09:36,008
他们是谁?
Who are they?

444
01:09:37,476 --> 01:09:39,026
他们是密苏里来的一个帮派。
They're a gang from Missouri.

445
01:09:40,025 --> 01:09:42,905
他们在战争中与匡特里尔的突袭者并肩作战。
They rode with Quantrill's Raiders during the war.

446
01:09:42,906 --> 01:09:44,739
船长是他的得力助手。
Captain was his right hand man.

447
01:09:46,415 --> 01:09:51,605
当老匡特里尔被杀或投降后，大多数人都放弃了。
Most of the fellers gave up when old Quantrill was killed or after the surrender.

448
01:09:51,606 --> 01:09:52,749
但不是队长。
But not Captain.

449
01:09:53,646 --> 01:09:55,358
战争对他来说永远不会结束。
The war ain't never ended for him.

450
01:10:00,276 --> 01:10:06,898
听着，如果如果我帮你，你能帮我和美国法警过个好日子吗?
Look, if if'n I help you, will you put in a good world with the US Marshall for me?

451
01:10:09,756 --> 01:10:11,859
好吧，这是我的计划。
Right then, here's my plan.

452
01:10:12,696 --> 01:10:16,294
其他人都在睡觉，我应该在值班。
The others are sleeping and I'm supposed to be on watch.

453
01:10:16,295 --> 01:10:21,605
如果你和孩子们能从窗户出去，我在大约一百步远的地方和你们会合。
If you and the young ones can get out of the window, I'll meet you back about a hundred paces.

454
01:10:21,606 --> 01:10:22,605
我把马。
I'll bring horses.

455
01:10:24,335 --> 01:10:25,804
你可以在不吵醒他们的情况下找到他们。
You can get 'em without waking them.

456
01:10:25,805 --> 01:10:27,806
我已经给他们准备好了。
I already done got 'em all saddled up.

457
01:10:35,166 --> 01:10:36,666
我去让孩子们准备好。
I'll get the children ready.

458
01:10:37,862 --> 01:10:39,299
我们10分钟后见。
We'll meet you in 10 minutes.

459
01:10:40,158 --> 01:10:43,634
好吧。
All right.

460
01:10:43,635 --> 01:10:44,523
谢谢你！
Thank you.

461
01:10:44,524 --> 01:10:50,199
我们可以在大家变聪明之前离开然后去找杰布。
And we can ride on out afore anyone's wiser and then go find Jeb.

462
01:10:57,545 --> 01:10:59,378
杰德!狗娘养的!
Jed! Son of a bitch!

463
01:11:01,356 --> 01:11:02,799
她抓住他了，上尉。
She got him, Captain.

464
01:11:04,956 --> 01:11:06,609
现在我得告诉他妈妈!
Now I gotta tell his mama!

465
01:11:08,166 --> 01:11:10,715
那个傻逼孩子根本不会撒谎!
That dang fool kid couldn't lie for shit!

466
01:11:10,716 --> 01:11:12,095
管好你的嘴。
You mind your tongue.

467
01:11:12,096 --> 01:11:14,409
妈，他只是想帮忙!
Ma, he was just trying to help!

468
01:11:19,746 --> 01:11:22,209
我从没告诉过他你爸的名字，一次都没有。
I never told him your pa's name, not one time.

469
01:11:23,496 --> 01:11:24,896
那他们是怎么知道的?
Then how did they know it?

470
01:11:26,338 --> 01:11:27,606
他们不是冲着我们来的。
They're not after us.

471
01:11:27,607 --> 01:11:29,106
他们来找你爸爸。
They came looking for your pa.

472
01:11:32,646 --> 01:11:35,255
所以他们才在外面慢慢来。
That's why they're out there taking their time.

473
01:11:35,256 --> 01:11:37,505
所以他们现在才在外面等着。
That's why they're out there now waiting.

474
01:11:37,506 --> 01:11:38,506
我们只是诱饵。
We're just the bait.

475
01:11:39,876 --> 01:11:41,549
你父亲正步入陷阱。
Your father's walking into a trap.

476
01:11:42,756 --> 01:11:46,998
威尔，我需要你做点事。
Will, I'm gonna need you to do something.

477
01:11:46,999 --> 01:11:48,839
你要有勇气去做。
And you're gonna have to be brave to do it.

478
01:11:50,916 --> 01:11:52,316
我需要你去找小牝马。
I need you to get the filly.

479
01:11:54,817 --> 01:11:57,928
什么?不,我不能。
What? No, I can't.

480
01:11:57,929 --> 01:11:59,482
是的,你可以。
Yes, you can.

481
01:11:59,483 --> 01:12:01,179
你是你父亲的儿子。
You're your father's son.

482
01:12:03,187 --> 01:12:05,149
该我们来保护他了。
It's our turn to protect him.

483
01:13:10,977 --> 01:13:15,977
那个美国佬小杂种!
That little Yankee bastard!

484
01:13:38,335 --> 01:13:47,951
他们带走了那个北方佬混蛋他们一枪爆了他的头把他烧了如果妈妈看到他死了
They took that Yankee bastard They shot him in the head They put him on the fire So if mama saw he's dead

485
01:13:53,893 --> 01:13:54,894
Sh !
Sh!

486
01:13:59,297 --> 01:14:01,047
没关系。没关系。
It's okay. It's okay.

487
01:14:06,365 --> 01:14:12,590
北方佬去了巴尔的摩他们遇到了一匹母马
The Yankee's went to Baltimore And they came upon a mare

488
01:14:51,336 --> 01:14:56,632
见鬼，上尉，马要奔向天国了!
Hell, Captain, the horses are running to kingdom come!

489
01:14:56,633 --> 01:14:59,257
你得到她!
You get her!

490
01:15:00,848 --> 01:15:01,848
哦,来吧。
Oh, come on.

491
01:15:08,137 --> 01:15:12,804
狗娘养的!回到这里。
Son of a bitch! Get back here.

492
01:15:15,358 --> 01:15:17,831
Will! Will!

493
01:15:19,148 --> 01:15:20,198
认为你会。
Think you're going.

494
01:15:22,785 --> 01:15:28,391
你知道吗，警监，他之前并没有伤害你的意思，但他现在有了。
You know, Captain, he didn't mean you no harm before, but he does now.

495
01:15:37,030 --> 01:15:38,030
放松。
Easy.

496
01:15:44,915 --> 01:15:46,536
不!不!
No! No!

497
01:15:46,537 --> 01:15:50,543
不!不!
No! No!

498
01:15:50,544 --> 01:15:53,838
你不要动。你理解我吗?
You don't move. You understand me?

499
01:15:53,839 --> 01:15:55,089
别动!
Don't you move!

500
01:15:56,509 --> 01:15:59,425
天啊，天啊，她打到我的脸了!
Oh my god, my god, she got my face!

501
01:16:00,801 --> 01:16:01,884
Will，跑!
Will, run!

502
01:16:02,793 --> 01:16:03,626
她打到我的脸了!
She got my face!

503
